Package: SAIGEgds
Type: Package
Title: Scalable Implementation of Generalized mixed models (SAIGE) using GDS files
Version: 0.9.7
Date: 2019-06-12
Depends: R (>= 3.0), gdsfmt (>= 1.10.0), SeqArray (>= 1.24.1), Rcpp
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo, RcppParallel
Imports: methods, RcppParallel, SPAtest
Suggests: parallel, crayon, RUnit, knitr, BiocGenerics
Authors@R: c(person("Xiuwen", "Zheng", role=c("aut", "cre"),
        email="xiuwen.zheng@abbvie.com"),
        person("Wei", "Zhou", role="ctb",
        comment="the original author of the SAIGE R package"),
        person("J. Wade", "Davis", role="ctb"))
Description: Scalable and accurate implementation of generalized mixed models
        with the support of Genomic Data Structure (GDS) files and highly optimized
        C++ implementation. It is designed for single variant tests in large-scale
        phenome-wide association studies (PheWAS) with millions of variants and
        thousands of samples.
License: GPL-3
SystemRequirements: C++11, GNU make
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: http://github.com/AbbVie-ComputationalGenomics/SAIGEgds
BugReports: http://github.com/AbbVie-ComputationalGenomics/SAIGEgds/issues
biocViews: Genetics, StatisticalMethod
